S|# docs/os/ — YVON OS Runtime Files|These are the live, mutable files that track YVON's current state across sessions. // They change frequently. Treat them as the OS mem — not documentation. // ---
S|Files|\| File \| Purpose \| When to read \| When to write \| // \|------\|---------\|-------------\|--------------\| // \| [`ses.md`](ses.md) \| Rolling log of the last 5 sessions — what happened, who did it, what's next \| Every ses start \| Every ses end (mandatory) \| // \| [`ctx.md`](ctx.md) \| Permanent architecture locks, vtr status, open strategic decisions \| When making architectural or strategic decisions \| Only when a dec is locked permanently \| // \| [`ROADMAP.md`](ROADMAP.md) \| Master 
S|archive/|Completed ses reports and one-off research documents. // Read-only — never updated, only appended when a ses report is archived. // \| File \| cnt \| // \|------\|---------\| // \| `2026-04-01-yvon-roadmap-full.md` \| Original master roadmap doc \| // \| `2026-04-05-mkt-dashboard-research.md` \| mkt dashboard research notes \| // \| `2026-04-08-complete-implementation-summary.md` \| Full 19-test implementation summary \| // \| `2026-04-08-enhanced-systems-implementation.md` \| Enhanced systems b
S|How these files relate to each other|``` // ses.md ← updated every ses, summarises what ctx.md decisions were acted on // ctx.md ← receives locked decisions that emerge from sessions // ROADMAP.md ← Diana + Marcus update when sprints close // USER.md    ← standalone, no dependencies — read cold at ses start // ``` // **ses.md is the source of truth.** If ses.md and an agt's own ses.md diverge, the agt's file wins. ses.md here is the global summary.